title: Google\Cloud\Optimization\V1\ShipmentModel\DurationDistanceMatrix
name: DurationDistanceMatrix
description:
Specifies a duration and distance matrix from visit and vehicle start locations to visit and vehicle end locations.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.optimization.v1.ShipmentModel.DurationDistanceMatrix

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.rows
params.description: Specifies the rows of the duration and distance matrix. It must have as many elements as [ShipmentModel.duration_distance_matrix_src_tags][google.cloud.optimization.v1.ShipmentModel.duration_distance_matrix_src_tags].

params.name: data.vehicle_start_tag
params.description: Tag defining to which vehicles this duration and distance matrix applies. If empty, this applies to all vehicles, and there can only be a single matrix. Each vehicle start must match exactly one matrix, i.e. exactly one of their start_tags field must match the vehicle_start_tag of a matrix (and of that matrix only). All matrices must have a different vehicle_start_tag.
